            "answer_text": "I Want To Hold Your Hand is the first No. 1 hit song of The Beatles in the US. That song was the one that started the \"Beatlemania\" and the \"British invasion\" within the US. The song entering the Billboard Hot 100 chart on 18 January 1964 at number 45. By 1 February it topped the Hot 100, and stayed there for seven weeks before being replaced by \"She Loves You\". It remained on the Billboard chart for 15 weeks. It was written by Lennon and McCartney because Brian Epstein asked them to write a song that would appeal the US audience after Capitol Records rejected the group's recordings in the US. ",
