            "answer_text": "\u201cI Want to Hold Your Hand\u201d became the first Beatles single to hit #1 in the U.S. on February 1st, 1964. Three weeks earlier, it had already hit the ground running entered in the #45 spot on the Billboard Hot 100. After it hit the #1 spot on February 1st, the song remained at #1 on the Billboard Hot 100 for seven more weeks, until it was overtaken by another Beatles hit: \u201cShe Loves You\u201d. \u201cI Want to Hold Your Hand\u201d hung on to the charts in lower spots for another fifteen weeks after that. Just a little slice of Beatlemania for ya. ",
